Great question! Decorators in Python can indeed be implemented in a class method by using the `@` symbol to attach the decorator to the class method. Here's an example:
```
class MyClass:
    def my_method(self):
        # This is the method that will be decorated
        pass

    @my_decorator
    def my_method(self):
        # This is the decorated method
        pass
```
